text: Parliamentary elections were held in Greece on 26 January 1936.Dieter Nohlen & Philip Stöver (2010) Elections in Europe: A data handbook, p830 The Liberal Party emerged as the largest party in Parliament, winning 126 of the 300 seats.Nohlen & Stöver, p859 ==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text- align:right !Party !Votes !% !Seats !+/– |- |align=left|Liberal Party||474,651||37.3||126||New |- |align=left|People's Party||281,597|||22.1||72||–183 |- |align=left|General Popular Radical Union||253,384||19.9||60||+28 |- |align=left|All People Front||73,411||5.8||15||New |- |align=left|Democratic Coalition||53,693||4.2||11||New |- |align=left|Freethinkers' Party||50,137||3.9||7||+1 |- |align=left|National Reform Party||17,822||1.4||4||New |- |align=left|Old Democratic Union of Crete||13,762||1.1||3||New |- |align=left|Hellenic Agricultural Party||13,006||1.0||1||New |- |align=left|Agricultural Democratic Party||12,333||1.0||1||New |- |align=left|Independents' Alliance||11,178||0.9||0||New |- |align=left|National Unionist Party||9,870||0.8||0||New |- |align=left|Communist Archio-Marxist Party of Greece||1,148||0.1||0||New |- |align=left|National Union of Greece||505||0.0||0||0 |- |align=left|Communist International Front||296||0.0||0||New |- |align=left|Independents||7,203||0.6||0||–6 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||4,083||–||–||– |- |align=left|Total||1,278,079||100||300||0 |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout|| || ||–||– |- |align=left colspan=5|Source: Nohlen & Stöver |} ==References== 1936 Category:1936 elections in Europe Legislative election Category:1930s in Greek politics Category:Eleftherios Venizelos Category:History of Greece (1924–1941) Category:January 1936 events
